  - m_Id: 5633206268862464
    m_Localized: Let's play !
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 5633317132705792
    m_Localized: Main Menu
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 5979416368390144
    m_Localized: Scoring
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 5979404783722496
    m_Localized: Game End
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 5979377558495232
    m_Localized: Constraints
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 5979021424336896
    m_Localized: Game Goal
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 5979432852004864
    m_Localized: The goal of the game is to get the highest score by placing the
      maximum number of the 21 pieces each player have on the board. The more squares
      the piece have, the more points they're valued.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 5979466377076736
    m_Localized: 'The play order is random.

      During first turn, and one after
      the other, each player place a piece on one of the highlighted cells of the
      board.

      Each consecutive turn, each new piece placed by a player must
      touch one of their own, only by the angle, not by the side.'
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 5979476313382912
    m_Localized: 'When a player can''t place any piece, he must select the PASS TURN
      button.

      Remaining players continues with the same turn order, until
      everyone has passed.'
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 5979486807531520
    m_Localized: 'Each square making a piece give 1 point to the player when placed.

      If
      every pieces are placed on teh board, a bonus of 15 points is given to the
      player.

      If the single square is the last placed piece, the bonus is
      20 points instead.


      The player with the hightest score is the winner
      !'
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 6882123123924992
    m_Localized: '{global.firstPlayerName} have {global.firstPlayerScore:plural:{}
      point |{} points}. Remaining pieces :'
    m_Metadata:
